AIM: A program to implement Matplotlib & Pandas libraries in python:

ALGORITHM: 

1. Start.
2. Import the pandas library for data handling 
  and matplotlib.pyplot for plotting.
3. Create a DataFrame (a table) containing columns with info.
4. Print the DataFrame to the console to verify the data.
5. Initialize a figure using plt.figure() to prepare the drawing area.
6. Create a Scatter Plot using the "Number" column for the X-axis and 
  the "Age" column for the Y-axis.
7. Label the graph:
 •Set the Title to "CON GRAPH".
 •Set the X-axis label to "Number".
 •Set the Y-axis label to "Age".
8. Display the plot using plt.show().
9. Stop.

